    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A narrative-driven, single-page application that guides the user through the story of Unidas' transformation. The structure flows from a high-level summary of the 'Two Unidas' concept, through the pivotal merger event, into detailed comparisons of pre- and post-merger performance via interactive charts. It culminates in a tabbed interactive section for deep-diving into specific risks (Credit, Liquidity, Market) and concludes with clear, card-based strategic recommendations. This structure was chosen to make a complex financial story digestible and engaging, prioritizing the narrative flow over a simple data dump, thus enhancing user understanding and retention. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - DRE Trends (Revenue/EBITDA): A line chart was chosen to clearly show the growth trend and the sharp structural break post-merger (Goal: Change). Interaction includes tooltips on hover. Library: Chart.js.
        - Leverage Ratio (Debt/EBITDA): A bar chart is used for direct period-to-period comparison, with the high-risk 2023 bar highlighted in a different color to emphasize the increased risk (Goal: Compare). Library: Chart.js.
        - Risk Analysis: An interactive tabbed component (HTML/CSS/JS) was selected to organize dense textual information cleanly, allowing users to explore detailed risks without overwhelming the UI (Goal: Organize).
        - Key Metrics & Recommendations: Presented in styled cards (HTML/Tailwind) to draw attention to the most critical takeaways and actionable insights (Goal: Inform).
        This approach uses the best visualization for each data type to support the overall narrative structure. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
